 congruence x^2 + 1 = 0 (mod 4) has NO solutions" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 32 "    (check by hand calculation)." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 62 "5. Now, because of 1 and \+
4 one can now say: if m is DIVISIBLE " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 62 "
    either by 4 OR by a prime p that is congruent to 3 mod 4, " }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 62 "    then the congruence x^2 + 1 = 0 (mod \+
m) has NO solutions. " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 49 "    SO, x^2 + 1 \+
= 0 (mod m) has no solutions for:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 80 "    \+
m = 3, 4, 6, 7, 8, 11, 12, 14, 15, 16, 18, 19, 20, 21, 22, 23, 24, 27,
 ... ." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 66 "In all of the above cases the maximum
 number of solutions was TWO." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 61 "Can ther
e ever be MORE than TWO solutions (for a QUADRATIC)? " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 
"" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 67 "Well, we know (should \+
or will) that for ANY quadratic congruence to" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 65 "a PRIME modulus p then - PROVIDING the coefficient of the
 squared" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 59 "term is NOT divisible by p - \+
the congruence has AT MOST two" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 33 "\"mutua
lly incongruent\" solutions." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 62 "However, when the modulus is COMPOSITE the numb
er of solutions" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 59 "CAN - in some special \+
cases - be MORE than two. An example:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "
" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 24 "msolve(x^2 + 1 = 0, 65);" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 62 "Some questions: How can o
